# anthropic claude models — current lineup
#
# the claude 4.x family. ids are what you pass to the api; claude code lets you
# toggle with /model. see also: [[ai-integration-skill]] [[ai-eval-skill]]
# [[claude-code]] [[ollama]]


# the three models

# - opus 4.7   — id: claude-opus-4-7
#   hardest reasoning, deep code, agentic workflows, research-grade tasks.
#   slowest and most expensive. use when capability matters more than throughput.
#
# - sonnet 4.6 — id: claude-sonnet-4-6
#   general coding, production workloads, balanced cost/quality. sweet spot for
#   most jobs; only falls short of opus on the genuinely hard stuff.
#
# - haiku 4.5  — id: claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
#   high-throughput classification, simple q&a, latency-sensitive ux. cheapest
#   and fastest. not the right pick for multi-step reasoning or nuanced code.


# how to choose

# - default to sonnet 4.6 for application work — it's the price/performance
#   baseline.
# - reach for opus 4.7 when a task is genuinely hard: long-horizon agentic
#   loops, gnarly debugging, design with real tradeoffs, or anything where a
#   sonnet failure would cost more than the price delta.
# - drop to haiku 4.5 when volume, latency, or unit economics dominate —
#   routing, tagging, short-content summarization, in-the-loop ui assistance.


# claude code specifics

# - opus 4.7 supports fast mode (/fast) — same opus model, faster output, no
#   downgrade to a smaller model. also available on opus 4.6.
# - switch models with /model inside claude code.


